<h2>&ldquo;PLAY TO GIVE&rdquo; WITH ELECTRONIC ARTS (EA) THIS WEEKEND TO BENEFIT PACER&rsquo;S NATIONAL BULLYING PREVENTION CENTER</h2>
<p>Minneapolis: PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center is pleased to announce a new partnership with global games company Electronic Arts (EA). On Friday, June 2, EA will launch its three-day &ldquo;Play to Give&rdquo; campaign. From Friday, June 2 through Sunday, June 4, players can celebrate Play to Give and promote inclusion and play by competing in-game challenges that yield special rewards.</p>
<p>&ldquo;We hope that players will also choose to make a donation to PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center as one of three charitable partners participating in Play to Give,&rdquo; said PACER Executive Director Paula Goldberg.</p>
<p> &ldquo;PACER Center feels so fortunate to have been chosen to partner with EA to help unite the world in creating kind, inclusive, and accepting communities and online environments that are safe and free from bullying,&rdquo; said Julie Hertzog, Director, PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center.</p>
<p>EA will be donating to three charitable partners, including PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center, that are already making a difference for a better internet. More details including Play to Give&rsquo;s results will be announced on Saturday, June 10 during EA Play in Hollywood, CA.</p>
